First Command Financial Planning

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
  (Redirected from First Command Financial Planning, Inc.)

					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


First Command Financial Planning, Inc.





Type

Privately held companies


Industry
Financial Planning


Founded
1958


Headquarters
Fort Worth, Texas



Key people

J. Scott Spiker, Chairman/Chief Executive Officer


Products
Mutual Funds, banking, life insurance


Website
www.firstcommand.com


First Command Financial Planning, Inc. is a broker-dealer registered with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), all 50 states, and the District of Columbia. It is a member of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation (SIPC).[1] First Command is recognized in the financial planning industry as an FPA Alliance firm, one of only two companies ever to receive this elite recognition from the 27,000-member Financial Planning Association.



